records.addlTxt:
Sentence is withheld and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two (2) years, consecutive to the prison sentence presently being served on 14 CF 461, to commence upon defendant's discharge date after extended supervision ends.
Conditions of probation:
1) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
2) maintain absolute sobriety;
3) maintain fulltime employment and/or schooling;
4) provide DNA sample and pay the surcharge;
5) pay court costs including $120.00 buy money to Metro Drug Unit;
6) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
Minutes.
